WEBVTT

01:31.007 --> 01:33.676
JAPAN'S CRIMINAL CONVICTION RATE IS 99.9%

01:43.686 --> 01:45.396
I had a cat.

01:47.023 --> 01:48.066
Go on.

01:49.109 --> 01:52.069
<i>All of a sudden, a cop came up to me…</i>

01:52.070 --> 01:54.905
<i>Then there were two, three of them…</i>

01:54.906 --> 01:57.992
<i>I thought, "If they arrest me like this,
my cat will die."</i>

01:58.785 --> 02:00.245
We weren't allowed to keep pets,

02:00.787 --> 02:03.414
and I was the only one who knew I had it.

02:04.499 --> 02:06.375
<i>Iwate Prefecture, Morioka City.</i>

02:06.376 --> 02:08.169
<i>March 2016.</i>

02:09.129 --> 02:10.629
<i>A young girl and her mother</i>

02:10.630 --> 02:13.967
<i>were found stabbed to death at home.</i>

02:15.760 --> 02:19.221
<i>The Morioka District Prosecutors' Office
indicted Keita Oe, who lived nearby,</i>

02:19.222 --> 02:22.975
<i>on suspicion of robbery and murder.</i>

02:22.976 --> 02:24.978
<i>Here's how he was arrested.</i>

02:25.603 --> 02:27.604
- <i>Oe fled during a police stop…</i>
- Hey, stop!

02:27.605 --> 02:29.940
- <i>…by a patrolling officer.</i>
- Hey, wait!

02:29.941 --> 02:31.401
<i>He ran into his house,</i>

02:32.443 --> 02:35.947
<i>and when officers followed him in,
they found a bloodstained knife.</i>

02:37.615 --> 02:38.908
<i>He was arrested on the spot.</i>

02:40.994 --> 02:42.870
- <i>Later DNA testing matched…</i>
- Hey! Settle down!

02:42.871 --> 02:46.249
<i>…the blood on the knife
used on the victims.</i>

02:47.959 --> 02:50.919
<i>Oe consistently denied the crime.</i>

02:50.920 --> 02:53.338
<i>and the knife, the key piece of evidence…</i>

02:53.339 --> 02:54.798
I found it.

02:54.799 --> 02:55.717
It's not mine.

02:56.885 --> 02:58.927
Come on, that doesn't add up.

02:58.928 --> 03:02.681
He refused the stop
because he felt guilty, right?

03:02.682 --> 03:03.599
HIGURUMA LAW OFFICE

03:03.600 --> 03:04.641
No.

03:04.642 --> 03:08.353
He was unfairly interrogated before

03:08.354 --> 03:10.564
because an acquaintance of his used drugs.

03:10.565 --> 03:12.983
So it was trauma?

03:12.984 --> 03:15.444
Even so,

03:15.445 --> 03:17.446
he "found" a bloody kitchen knife?

03:17.447 --> 03:18.573
Why?

03:19.073 --> 03:22.200
He says he planned to
turn it in to the police later.

03:22.201 --> 03:23.369
Later?

03:24.579 --> 03:27.624
I know.
Every part of his story sounds forced.

03:28.249 --> 03:30.542
But if you consider his situation…

03:30.543 --> 03:34.379
He is a live-in worker at an NPO.

03:34.380 --> 03:37.132
It starts to feel
like it isn't impossible.

03:37.133 --> 03:39.052
An NPO?

03:40.011 --> 03:43.096
<i>They mainly run shelters and support</i>

03:43.097 --> 03:45.641
<i>elderly people with nowhere to go.</i>

03:45.642 --> 03:48.853
<i>Oe worked there, taking care of them.</i>

03:49.604 --> 03:52.106
But he wasn't paid a salary.

03:52.899 --> 03:55.692
<i>They call it "allowances."
He gets New Year's money sometimes,</i>

03:55.693 --> 03:58.695
<i>or boxed lunches and ingredients.
That's it.</i>

03:58.696 --> 04:00.197
<i>And despite that,</i>

04:00.198 --> 04:03.992
<i>they charge him 50,000 yen a month
as "rent."</i>

04:03.993 --> 04:05.535
That's brutal…

04:05.536 --> 04:09.122
A lot of the residents there
have criminal records.

04:09.123 --> 04:12.585
As for why he was late
turning in the weapon he found…

04:13.169 --> 04:16.589
We weren't allowed to call them.
Patrol cars or ambulances.

04:17.173 --> 04:19.217
It would bother the neighbors.

04:20.927 --> 04:24.346
That organization sounds pretty shady.

04:24.347 --> 04:27.141
Yes. It's gray, almost black.

04:28.142 --> 04:31.895
Ever since disaster relief money
started flowing into Tohoku,

04:31.896 --> 04:35.358
these shady NPOs have been increasing.

04:35.942 --> 04:38.152
So a weapon lying around
isn't that far-fetched.

04:39.279 --> 04:42.532
There's more than enough chance
Oe is innocent.

04:44.325 --> 04:47.536
First, we dig into the group.
Their activity record, tax filings,

04:47.537 --> 04:50.372
and the identities of every resident.

04:50.373 --> 04:53.417
I'll keep questioning Oe.

04:53.418 --> 04:55.252
Shimizu, you keep investigating.

04:55.253 --> 04:58.715
Isn't my workload
increasing all of a sudden?

05:00.717 --> 05:02.467
Also, can you keep a cat?

05:02.468 --> 05:03.303
A cat?

05:04.387 --> 05:07.724
<i>Court appointments pay peanuts,
but they dump a ton of work on you.</i>

05:08.349 --> 05:10.600
<i>And public opinion is all "guilty."</i>

05:10.601 --> 05:15.022
<i>Plus, it's murder. No suspended sentence,
and the death penalty is possible.</i>

05:15.023 --> 05:16.691
<i>You do all this, and for what?</i>

05:18.192 --> 05:20.193
Mr. Higuruma,

05:20.194 --> 05:22.988
why did you take a case like this?

05:22.989 --> 05:25.073
It's fine once in a while.

05:25.074 --> 05:27.493
If I only do easy work,
my skills get dull.

05:28.077 --> 05:30.037
<i>"Once in a while"?</i>

05:30.038 --> 05:32.040
This isn't once in a while!

05:32.582 --> 05:34.709
What you're thinking
is all over your face.

05:37.211 --> 05:39.797
Higuruma, you never change.

05:40.798 --> 05:44.010
It's rough when the boss attorney
doesn't care about money.

05:44.510 --> 05:46.053
I'm not saying

05:46.054 --> 05:49.598
he should run a café on the side
like you, Ms. Takagi…

05:49.599 --> 05:51.516
But you said he never changes…

05:51.517 --> 05:53.853
Was Mr. Higuruma always like that?

05:55.063 --> 05:56.354
Not really.

05:56.355 --> 05:58.524
If anything, he's worse now.

05:59.067 --> 05:59.984
What?

06:00.610 --> 06:02.486
Back when he was at our firm,

06:02.487 --> 06:05.614
he handled a case
for reckless driving causing injury.

06:05.615 --> 06:07.408
Drunk driving, I mean.

06:08.534 --> 06:10.744
The defendant was 19 years old.

06:10.745 --> 06:12.287
People at work

06:12.288 --> 06:15.540
forced him to drink and drive.

06:15.541 --> 06:18.293
But they made everyone match
their testimonies.

06:18.294 --> 06:20.170
He couldn't come up with a settlement

06:20.171 --> 06:22.632
or get a suspended sentence.

06:28.596 --> 06:29.764
Liar…

06:31.390 --> 06:34.060
You said I would be found not guilty!

06:35.103 --> 06:38.897
You said
you would try to get him probation.

06:38.898 --> 06:41.526
You never said he would be found
not guilty, though.

06:42.193 --> 06:43.944
That should have taught you, right?

06:43.945 --> 06:47.115
Quit taking hopeless criminal cases.

06:47.782 --> 06:49.658
Saving the weak…

06:49.659 --> 06:52.202
Sure, it sounds noble.

06:52.203 --> 06:54.663
But on our own, without the court

06:54.664 --> 06:56.581
and prosecutors, there are limits.

06:56.582 --> 06:57.791
Oh, I found it!

06:57.792 --> 07:00.962
You don't need to go that far.
Even the clients would resent you.

07:03.047 --> 07:04.673
They are cornered,

07:04.674 --> 07:07.218
financially and mentally.

07:07.760 --> 07:09.846
It is no surprise they lash out at me.

07:12.306 --> 07:15.560
What is in your heart, Higuruma?

07:16.727 --> 07:17.562
I…

07:40.042 --> 07:42.879
The ruling. The defendant is…

07:43.463 --> 07:44.421
Not guilty.

07:44.422 --> 07:45.506
What?

07:46.466 --> 07:48.133
What's going on?

07:48.134 --> 07:49.260
No way…

07:49.844 --> 07:51.637
We actually won…

07:53.639 --> 07:54.891
Not yet.

07:56.434 --> 07:58.435
They will appeal right away.

07:58.436 --> 07:59.269
THE MORIOKA MOTHER AND CHILD MURDER CASE-
NOT GUILTY VERDICT DESPITE SUSPICIONS

07:59.270 --> 07:59.854
FORMER JUDGE WAS SHOCKED
AT NOT GUILTY VERDICT DESPITE EVIDENCE

08:01.731 --> 08:02.606
NOT GUILTY
IF YOU PAY, YOU'RE NOT GUILTY

08:02.607 --> 08:03.357
HOW MUCH WAS IT? LAW IS DEAD.
PROSECUTOR IS USELESS

08:03.941 --> 08:05.109
<i>Next, the prosecutors…</i>

08:14.494 --> 08:18.830
<i>The stolen items were not found
in Mr. Oe's room.</i>

08:18.831 --> 08:20.415
<i>Someone at the NPO</i>

08:20.416 --> 08:23.711
<i>went missing right after the crime.</i>

08:24.295 --> 08:27.672
Also, at the estimated time of the crime,

08:27.673 --> 08:30.467
the security camera at the shop

08:30.468 --> 08:32.053
showed you there.
That's the biggest problem.

08:32.595 --> 08:35.640
Good thing you do not cook, Mr. Oe.

08:36.224 --> 08:39.644
Mr. Higuruma, sir. Thank you so much.

08:40.228 --> 08:42.687
Don't call me "sir."

08:42.688 --> 08:45.441
And do not get ahead of yourself.
There is still the appeal.

08:46.067 --> 08:46.983
I WAS NERVOUS, TOO

08:46.984 --> 08:48.528
It's not that.

08:51.239 --> 08:54.116
Thank you for believing in me.

08:57.578 --> 09:00.080
APPEAL TRIAL-SECOND TRIAL

09:00.081 --> 09:03.000
LIFE IMPRISONMENT

09:03.668 --> 09:05.377
<i>The defense has to work</i>

09:05.378 --> 09:08.380
<i>with limited budget and staff.</i>

09:08.381 --> 09:12.467
<i>The prosecution pours in taxes
and manpower to build evidence.</i>

09:12.468 --> 09:14.720
<i>That is fine. That is how it works.</i>

09:15.346 --> 09:16.721
<i>But in the appeal,</i>

09:16.722 --> 09:20.393
<i>the prosecution added no new evidence.</i>

09:22.520 --> 09:26.189
<i>Yet they ruled,
"There is no reason to suspect</i>

09:26.190 --> 09:28.525
<i>the missing person.
The investigation was reckless."</i>

09:28.526 --> 09:30.403
<i>And the verdict was overturned.</i>

09:32.655 --> 09:35.657
<i>The Supreme Court is a narrow gate.</i>

09:35.658 --> 09:37.785
<i>Most appeals are rejected outright.</i>

09:38.286 --> 09:41.038
<i>It is hard to even get a proper hearing.</i>

09:42.206 --> 09:45.501
<i>This trial was guilty from the start…</i>

09:52.925 --> 09:53.968
<i>Why are you looking at me…</i>

09:56.304 --> 09:57.597
<i>with those eyes?</i>

10:00.766 --> 10:03.019
<i>What is in your heart,</i>

10:03.561 --> 10:04.770
Higuruma?

10:06.772 --> 10:10.109
I'm not some champion saving the weak.

10:11.152 --> 10:15.656
Since I was young,
I could not ignore what I felt was wrong.

10:16.407 --> 10:18.659
That is all.

10:19.660 --> 10:23.872
The Lady of Justice blinds herself
for equality under the law.

10:23.873 --> 10:25.915
But people shut their eyes

10:25.916 --> 10:27.501
<i>to anything, to protect themselves.</i>

10:28.210 --> 10:32.423
So I will not shake off
the hands that cling to me.

10:36.344 --> 10:38.929
I want to be the one
who keeps her eyes open.

10:43.309 --> 10:45.852
If you object to this ruling,

10:45.853 --> 10:47.937
file a notice of appeal

10:47.938 --> 10:50.566
within 15 days, including today.

11:02.203 --> 11:04.163
Mr. Higuruma?

11:07.541 --> 11:09.418
Everyone, dismissed.

11:14.590 --> 11:16.092
Start over.

11:16.592 --> 11:17.550
CULLING GAME PLAYER

11:17.551 --> 11:20.303
HIROMI HIGURUMA

11:20.304 --> 11:21.554
<i>Higuruma is…</i>

11:21.555 --> 11:23.974
- in Shinjuku.
-…in Ikebukuro.

11:24.600 --> 11:26.059
Shinjuku…

11:26.060 --> 11:28.228
<i>I hope Itadori is headed there too.</i>

11:28.229 --> 11:29.813
Ikebukuro?

11:29.814 --> 11:31.273
<i>Maybe Fushiguro is there too.</i>

11:35.569 --> 11:38.071
Isn't he a little late?

11:38.072 --> 11:40.573
When is that kid going to bring me

11:40.574 --> 11:44.453
the next sucker?

11:51.585 --> 11:54.337
Huh? What?

11:54.338 --> 11:57.882
No. That's not it.

11:57.883 --> 12:00.553
Hey, what are you doing?

12:01.095 --> 12:02.304
<i>Like this.</i>

12:04.432 --> 12:05.890
<i>Why are you being so quiet?</i>

12:05.891 --> 12:08.811
<i>- Just grin and laugh along.</i>
- What's your problem?

12:09.770 --> 12:11.480
All right.

12:12.314 --> 12:14.274
<i>- Yes, don't talk back.</i>
- What is your problem?

12:14.275 --> 12:15.024
What is it?

12:15.025 --> 12:16.985
<i>- I didn't say it, but…</i>
- Hey!

12:16.986 --> 12:20.822
- <i>Why doesn't he get it? Is he stupid?</i>
- What? That's not enough?

12:20.823 --> 12:23.908
<i>They aren't good at school</i>

12:23.909 --> 12:26.578
- <i>or sports, but they've got pride.</i>
- Come on!

12:26.579 --> 12:28.580
<i>So don't bruise their egos.</i>

12:28.581 --> 12:30.791
<i>- Just laugh and play along.</i>
- Come on!

12:31.792 --> 12:35.378
<i>Then the others won't target you.</i>

12:35.379 --> 12:37.756
- <i>And once in a while, you might get lucky.</i>
- What do you think?

12:38.507 --> 12:39.884
Stop it.

12:43.262 --> 12:45.013
<i>Another idiot…</i>

12:45.014 --> 12:47.557
That uniform… West Junior High?

12:47.558 --> 12:49.350
A middle-school kid?

12:49.351 --> 12:51.811
He talked back.

12:51.812 --> 12:54.481
So, for you…

12:54.482 --> 12:55.608
Guidance is needed!

13:02.740 --> 13:03.908
What?

13:11.499 --> 13:13.501
Say no to violence!

13:30.476 --> 13:31.643
You…

13:31.644 --> 13:32.561
CULLING GAME PLAYER

13:35.064 --> 13:36.773
Me?

13:36.774 --> 13:38.107
YUJI ITADORI RIN AMAI

13:38.108 --> 13:40.360
- Hey.
- What?

13:40.361 --> 13:43.572
If you're going to Shinjuku
through Ikebukuro, don't.

13:44.156 --> 13:45.908
This area has a lot of supplies.

13:46.492 --> 13:48.577
You're more likely to run into players.

13:49.161 --> 13:51.663
I have two reasons to refuse.

13:51.664 --> 13:53.748
The route is easy to follow.

13:53.749 --> 13:55.960
And my base is nearby.

13:57.628 --> 13:59.879
Let me at least take a shower.

13:59.880 --> 14:02.508
I haven't really rested since yesterday.

14:05.594 --> 14:08.555
Higuruma is using this theater as a base.

14:08.556 --> 14:10.473
If he hasn't moved, anyway.

14:10.474 --> 14:13.226
Oh, right! Seriously, that helps.

14:13.227 --> 14:14.270
Thanks.

14:14.812 --> 14:17.480
Hey, wait!

14:17.481 --> 14:18.566
What?

14:19.066 --> 14:20.775
Are you really going?

14:20.776 --> 14:24.405
I want to regroup, but we're in a hurry.

14:25.030 --> 14:27.699
I've never met Higuruma,

14:27.700 --> 14:30.994
but Haba got totally wrecked by him once.

14:30.995 --> 14:32.829
Then we're fine.

14:32.830 --> 14:34.247
I beat Propeller Head.

14:34.248 --> 14:37.000
- I can at least run away, right?
- What?

14:37.001 --> 14:38.084
MAYBE…

14:38.085 --> 14:39.461
See you!

14:40.754 --> 14:42.172
<i>Say it…</i>

14:43.465 --> 14:45.175
<i>I have to say it…</i>

14:45.885 --> 14:47.928
<i>Let's stop doing this…</i>

14:53.726 --> 14:54.643
<i>Sorry.</i>

14:56.270 --> 14:57.187
<i>Itadori…</i>

15:00.274 --> 15:03.484
Higuruma? Yes…

15:03.485 --> 15:08.239
Sorry, but I'm Reggie.

15:08.240 --> 15:10.409
You got played.

15:13.746 --> 15:17.999
What's with that face?
That's not scary at all.

15:18.000 --> 15:20.169
- And just so you know, Reggie--
- Don't talk.

15:27.217 --> 15:28.928
You're wasting time.

15:39.939 --> 15:43.067
Who are you? What are you doing there?

15:45.402 --> 15:46.487
And you?

15:49.406 --> 15:53.117
Have you ever taken a bath
with your clothes on?

15:53.118 --> 15:54.119
No.

15:55.079 --> 15:57.915
It feels better than I expected.

16:00.751 --> 16:01.585
Right.

16:03.754 --> 16:05.630
Back in primary school,

16:05.631 --> 16:08.968
I liked clothed swimming lessons.

16:09.551 --> 16:13.096
Lately, nothing really matters to me.

16:13.097 --> 16:17.600
So I've been trying things
I told myself I shouldn't do.

16:17.601 --> 16:21.020
Guess I went bad after 30.

16:21.021 --> 16:22.147
Funny?

16:22.815 --> 16:24.566
It's a little funny.

16:25.317 --> 16:26.986
You are Higuruma, right?

16:27.653 --> 16:29.905
- Correct.
- I want to talk.

16:31.031 --> 16:32.866
Wait.

16:33.534 --> 16:35.243
I'm a lawyer.

16:35.244 --> 16:39.706
Talking to me costs
a 5,000 yen consulting fee per 30 minutes.

16:39.707 --> 16:41.083
What?

16:42.376 --> 16:44.085
Kidding.

16:44.086 --> 16:47.089
I felt like playing
a slightly annoying lawyer.

16:48.048 --> 16:49.299
<i>Right…</i>

16:50.217 --> 16:52.011
<i>For awhile, this guy…</i>

16:52.845 --> 16:54.722
You've got 100 points, right?

16:55.514 --> 16:57.558
<i>He's not a reincarnated sorcerer.</i>

16:58.142 --> 17:01.060
<i>He's a modern sorcerer
whose technique awakened.</i>

17:01.061 --> 17:04.397
<i>He'll listen. There's room to negotiate!</i>

17:04.398 --> 17:07.233
Yes. You pass.

17:07.234 --> 17:10.194
<i>- What?
- All right, I get it.</i>

17:10.195 --> 17:13.781
<i>That</i> shikigami <i>is the real deal.
You're strong, right?</i>

17:13.782 --> 17:16.994
<i>If you were weak,
I would have used you and killed you.</i>

17:17.494 --> 17:19.912
<i>I like you. Join my team.</i>

17:19.913 --> 17:22.916
<i>What's that? Nobody told me.</i>

17:24.251 --> 17:26.044
What are you planning?

17:26.045 --> 17:29.673
How much do you know
about the Culling Game?

17:30.424 --> 17:31.633
It's a ritual, isn't it?

17:32.217 --> 17:35.428
Using players' cursed energy

17:35.429 --> 17:38.056
to ferry Japan's people to the other side,

17:38.057 --> 17:40.267
and turn them into something else.

17:40.976 --> 17:43.062
<i>Should we keep Tengen out of this?</i>

17:43.604 --> 17:47.899
- What, you know Kenjaku?
- What?

17:47.900 --> 17:49.777
<i>Figured there would be sorcerers</i>

17:50.444 --> 17:52.738
<i>connected to Kenjaku…</i>

17:53.781 --> 17:55.949
So, in short…

17:56.909 --> 17:59.953
we want to end the Culling Game.

18:01.038 --> 18:03.664
Wait, time out. Not "end it," exactly.

18:03.665 --> 18:06.167
We want to nullify forced killing.

18:06.168 --> 18:07.877
To add a rule,

18:07.878 --> 18:10.005
let us use your 100 points.

18:10.631 --> 18:12.382
I'll be brief.

18:13.217 --> 18:14.301
I refuse.

18:16.053 --> 18:17.471
Was that a joke too?

18:18.388 --> 18:22.725
No. I simply see potential
in the Culling Game.

18:22.726 --> 18:23.434
STATUTE BOOKS

18:23.435 --> 18:25.186
Sometimes the law is powerless.

18:25.187 --> 18:28.648
But, what about the Culling Game's rules?

18:28.649 --> 18:31.317
If the jujutsu I was given is real,

18:31.318 --> 18:33.111
then the rules are real too, right?

18:33.112 --> 18:37.698
That "using players' cursed energy" bit
you mentioned…

18:37.699 --> 18:39.367
That's probably a bluff.

18:39.368 --> 18:40.326
What?

18:40.327 --> 18:42.286
Not exactly a bluff.

18:42.287 --> 18:45.540
More like plan B or plan C.

18:45.541 --> 18:47.292
I've got three reasons.

18:47.876 --> 18:51.295
The number of players.
The gap in strength between players.

18:51.296 --> 18:52.798
And the barrier's rules.

18:53.632 --> 18:55.466
<i>Say there are about 1,000 players</i>

18:55.467 --> 18:58.636
<i>split evenly across ten colonies.</i>

18:58.637 --> 19:00.888
<i>That's about 100 per colony.</i>

19:00.889 --> 19:03.891
<i>But among sorcerers,</i>

19:03.892 --> 19:07.979
<i>there are freaks like Kashimo
and Higuruma.</i>

19:07.980 --> 19:11.941
<i>Those two alone have already culled
about 60 sorcerers.</i>

19:11.942 --> 19:15.320
<i>There's probably at least one like that
in every colony.</i>

19:15.904 --> 19:18.906
So even from early on,
only the strong remain,

19:18.907 --> 19:21.160
and the Culling Game stalls out?

19:21.952 --> 19:23.579
<i>Yes. I had felt it.</i>

19:24.413 --> 19:26.330
<i>It's too quiet in here!</i>

19:26.331 --> 19:28.166
It already has.

19:28.167 --> 19:31.169
At least in Tokyo Colony One.

19:31.170 --> 19:34.964
And the teleportation on entry.

19:34.965 --> 19:37.091
Sure, it spreads people out.

19:37.092 --> 19:39.093
<i>But mainly, it pushes modern sorcerers</i>

19:39.094 --> 19:41.596
<i>into an early second awakening.</i>

19:41.597 --> 19:44.348
<i>Some people even die from teleportation.</i>

19:44.349 --> 19:47.351
<i>If Kenjaku really wanted
their cursed energy,</i>

19:47.352 --> 19:50.021
<i>he would want more sorcerers.</i>

19:50.022 --> 19:52.607
<i>And he would want them fighting longer,
dragging it out.</i>

19:52.608 --> 19:55.193
No complaints and prosecutions needed.

19:55.194 --> 19:57.486
What if anyone who breaks the rules

19:57.487 --> 20:01.490
will be punished, like the law of physics?

20:01.491 --> 20:03.826
Wouldn't that be wonderful?

20:03.827 --> 20:06.078
Sure, the general rules have problems.

20:06.079 --> 20:09.332
But I want to watch the barrier system.

20:09.333 --> 20:11.752
I can't have it ending too soon.

20:12.336 --> 20:14.295
Especially the confiscation of techniques

20:14.296 --> 20:17.507
in Rules Two and Eight.

20:18.133 --> 20:21.344
Rule-wise, if your technique
is confiscated, you'll probably die.

20:21.345 --> 20:24.472
The Culling Game itself is a ritual.

20:24.473 --> 20:27.099
If we screw around,
everyone in this country will die.

20:27.100 --> 20:28.935
That's bogus.

20:28.936 --> 20:31.771
The Culling Game claims
it will go on forever.

20:31.772 --> 20:34.191
<i>I don't totally get that either.</i>

20:36.735 --> 20:38.445
I'll put it differently.

20:39.154 --> 20:42.574
Let me use your 100 points, Higuruma.

20:43.742 --> 20:47.621
Ever killed someone you didn't like?

20:50.832 --> 20:52.501
It feels better

20:53.335 --> 20:55.337
than I expected.

20:56.338 --> 20:57.464
<i>Shikigami…</i>

20:58.632 --> 21:00.341
<i>Higuruma has 100 points.</i>

21:00.342 --> 21:02.844
<i>He might have killed 20 sorcerers.</i>

21:03.345 --> 21:06.640
<i>I can't rush in.</i>

21:07.224 --> 21:09.351
<i>I'll handle whatever he throws at me.</i>

21:11.436 --> 21:12.729
Domain Expansion.

21:13.689 --> 21:15.774
Deadly Sentencing.

21:28.161 --> 21:30.997
<i>That "forever" clause is just a cover</i>

21:30.998 --> 21:33.457
<i>for the real plan.</i>

21:33.458 --> 21:35.793
<i>I'm sure of it.</i>

21:35.794 --> 21:40.715
<i>Once only the strong are left,
Kenjaku will drop a bomb on the game…</i>

21:40.716 --> 21:44.303
<i>And the Culling Game is done.
Its role will be over.</i>

21:55.856 --> 21:57.524
SIT DOWN

22:06.742 --> 22:08.285
THANKS FOR INVITING ME

23:41.962 --> 23:43.546
<i>All right. Make your excuse.</i>

23:43.547 --> 23:45.756
- <i>What happens if I'm found guilty?
- Judgeman, begin.</i>

23:45.757 --> 23:46.674
<i>So it's okay to lie?</i>

23:46.675 --> 23:48.717
<i>You get one chance to testify.</i>

23:48.718 --> 23:49.718
<i>I can't knead my cursed energy!</i>

23:49.719 --> 23:52.638
<i>How are you keeping up with me,
without cursed energy?</i>

23:52.639 --> 23:54.807
<i>Do it over! One more time!</i>

23:54.808 --> 23:55.934
NEXT EPISODE
